        ")) (entry nil (id nil "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/q/30332") (rank ((scheme . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com")) "2") (title ((type . "text")) "Evil-leader stops working when I eval-buffer") (category ((scheme . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/tags") (term . "evil"))) (author nil (name nil "Daniel Satanove") (uri nil "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/users/14759")) (link ((rel . "alternate") (href . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/30332/evil-leader-stops-working-when-i-eval-buffer"))) (published nil "2017-01-31T20:39:28Z") (updated nil "2017-02-10T15:15:51Z") (summary ((type . "html")) "

            <p>If I load up emacs and go to my .emacs file (a fragment of which is given below), and I press SPC f or C-c C-f then it does find-file, which is the expected behaviour. However, if I type M-x eval-buffer, or load-file, suddenly SPC f doesn't work, but C-c C-f still does. If I press SPC, it just goes to the next character as it would without evil-leader. What gives?</p>

<pre><code>(require 'evil) 
(evil-mode 1)

(require 'evil-leader)
(global-evil-leader-mode)

(evil-leader/set-leader \"&lt;SPC&gt;\")

(evil-leader/set-key \"f\" 'find-file)
