<p>I have tried the following:</p>
<pre><code>(defun init-python-mode ()
(when (fboundp 'electric-indent-mode)
(electric-indent-mode -1))
;; The following doesn't work to ensure C-j does the right thing.
(define-key python-mode-map (kbd \"C-j\") 'newline-and-indent)
(define-key python-mode-map (kbd \"RET\") 'newline-indent)
(local-set-key (kbd \"C-j\") 'newline-and-indent)
(local-set-key (kbd \"RET\") 'newline)
;; ... so we're having to resort to using a hack.
(run-at-time \"1 sec\" nil
(lambda()
(local-set-key (kbd \"C-j\") 'newline-and-indent)
(local-set-key (kbd \"RET\") 'newline)))
)
</code></pre>
<p>As you can see above, I could only set the key bindings after running a timer for a second.  It's as if additional code runs after my python initialisation function that overrides any attempts to locally bind the <code>C-j</code> and <code>RET</code> keys.</p>
