        "))) ("Get time in AM/PM format" "<p><code>(format-time-string \"%p\")</code> is empty in my Emacs. How I can format date in AM/PM format?</p>
<p>That answer second part of <a href=\"http://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/20799/show-time-in-different-time-zones\">Show time in different time zones</a></p>
<p><strong>UPDATE</strong></p>
<pre><code>(length (format-time-string \"%p\"))  ; is 0
(getenv \"LC_TIME\")                  ; is \"en_DK.utf8\"
</code></pre>
<p>My default preferences (in <code>.emacs</code>):</p>
<pre><code>(setq display-time-24hr-format t)
