</code></pre>" "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/20810/get-time-in-am-pm-format" (22712 46555) old 23 nil nil ((guid nil "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/q/20810") (id nil "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/q/20810") (rank ((scheme . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com")) "2") (title ((type . "text")) "Get time in AM/PM format") (category ((scheme . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/tags") (term . "time-date"))) (author nil (name nil "gavenkoa") (uri nil "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/users/947")) (link ((rel . "alternate") (href . "http://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/20810/get-time-in-am-pm-format"))) (published nil "2016-03-07T09:59:15Z") (updated nil "2017-03-03T00:16:27Z") (summary ((type . "html")) "

            <p><code>(format-time-string \"%p\")</code> is empty in my Emacs. How I can format date in AM/PM format?</p>

<p>That answer second part of <a href=\"http://emacs.stackexchange.com/questions/20799/show-time-in-different-time-zones\">Show time in different time zones</a></p>

<p><strong>UPDATE</strong></p>

<pre><code>(length (format-time-string \"%p\"))  ; is 0
(getenv \"LC_TIME\")                  ; is \"en_DK.utf8\"
</code></pre>

<p>My default preferences (in <code>.emacs</code>):</p>

<pre><code>(setq display-time-24hr-format t)
(setq display-time-day-and-date nil)
</code></pre>

